  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This chapter does not contain a \"calendar of feasts,\" or a summary and completion of the directions previously given in a scattered form concerning the festal times of Israel, but simply a list of those festal days and periods of the year at which holy meetings were to be held. This is most clearly stated in the heading (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 23:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): \"the festal times of Jehovah, which ye shall call out as holy meetings, these are they, My feasts,\" i.e., those which are to be regarded as My feasts, sanctified to Me. The festal seasons and days were called \"feasts of Jehovah,\" times appointed and fixed by Jehovah (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), not because the feasts belonged to fixed times regulated by the course of the moon (Knobel), but because Jehovah had appointed them as days, or times, which were to be sanctified to Him. Hence the expression is not only used with reference to the Sabbath, the new moon, and the other yearly feasts; but in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 28:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 29:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is extended so as to include the times of the daily morning and evening sacrifice. (On the \"holy convocation\" see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 12:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
